  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a post-market study of the Rebound Hernia Repair Device to further establish the
      safety, efficacy, and utility of the Rebound Hernia Repair Device in a controlled population.
      The Rebound Hernia Repair Device will be used for its approved indication in comparison to
      &quot;standard&quot; hernia mesh. Two-way students t-tests, Chi squared analysis and ANOVA will be used
      to detect differences in variables. The study is sufficiently powered to detect a 25%
      difference.

      The study data will include quality of life assessments, visual analogue scale , SF-36,
      Carolinas Comfort Scale), recurrence of hernia (technical failure), use of medications (pain)
      and complications/adverse events.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
